  "texts": [
    "Within the co-occurring word cloud of the Xiongnu (匈奴), a nomadic ethnic group active during the Han dynasty, numerous negative terms related to war, such as '杀 (kill)' and '死 (death)' are prominent.",
    "In contrast, during the Yuan dynasty, when the Mongols replaced the Han Nationality regime to become China's rulers, the co-occurring vocabulary was predominantly associated with political affairs, with fewer negative terms.",
    "HUMANITIES AND SOCIAL SCIENCES COMMUNICATIONS | https://doi.org/10.1057/s41599-024-02763-6 ARTICLE HUMANITIES AND SOCIAL SCIENCES COMMUNICATIONS | (2024) 11:291 | https://doi.org/10.1057/s41599-024-02763-6",
    "To examine these changes across a broader timespan, we shifted our focus to a more diverse range of ethnic groups.",
    "The diachronic frequency of various ethnic groups is depicted in Fig. 9c, and we employed this result, in conjunction with historical common sense, to determine the active periods of each group."
  ]
}